---
@META
dir: skillsPraut/src/hooks/
updated: 2026-04-13
files: 6
stack: TypeScript, Remotion

@EXPORTS
easings.ts: easings — 3 sanctioned easing curves (linear | out | standard)
interpolateColors.ts: interpolateColors — linear hex color interpolation
useCountUp.ts: useCountUp — spring-based count-up animation hook
useScaleToFit.ts: useScaleToFit — scale factor for reference→actual dimensions
useStaggeredAnimation.ts: useStaggeredAnimation — (index)→progress stagger mapper
useTypewriter.ts: useTypewriter — character-by-character typing effect

@FUNCTIONS
interpolateColors(t:number, from:string, to:string) → string
  purpose: lerp between two #RRGGBB hex colors
  side-effects: none

useCountUp({from?,to,startFrame?,config?}) → number
  purpose: animated numeric count-up via spring
  side-effects: none

useScaleToFit(refW?:number, refH?:number) → number
  purpose: scale 1920x1080 reference to actual composition size
  side-effects: none

useStaggeredAnimation({staggerFrames?,startFrame?,config?}) → (index:number)→number
  purpose: staggered spring progress per list item index
  side-effects: none

useTypewriter({fullText,pauseAfter?,charFrames?,pauseSeconds?}) → string
  purpose: typewriter substring at current frame
  side-effects: none

@DEPENDENCIES
internal: styles/tokens (springs, timing, frame)
external: remotion (spring, useCurrentFrame, useVideoConfig, Easing, interpolate)

@STANDARDS
- All hooks use tokens.springs/timing defaults
- No custom easing — use easings.ts only (linear | out | standard)
- Deterministic output per frame — stable across renders
- useCountUp defaults to springs.smooth
- useStaggeredAnimation defaults to timing.fast (12f) stagger
- useTypewriter defaults to 2 frames per character
---
